1
00:00:44,253 --> 00:00:46,338
ANNOUNCER [ON TV]: Now here comes
the president's helicopter...

2
00:00:46,505 --> 00:00:47,756
...Marine Helicopter Number 1...

3
00:00:47,924 --> 00:00:52,302
...landing in the plaza on the east side
of the east front of the Capitol.

4
00:00:52,470 --> 00:00:56,473
The helicopter hovering gently
just off the ground.

5
00:00:56,641 --> 00:00:57,682
Amazing timing.

6
00:00:57,850 --> 00:01:00,268
The president flying
all the way across the world...

7
00:01:00,436 --> 00:01:03,772
...across the Atlantic Ocean,
arriving almost exactly...

8
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:07,984
Exactly as scheduled,
at 9:30 in the Capitol plaza...

9
00:01:08,152 --> 00:01:11,071
...so he can go up the steps
of the House of Representatives...

10
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:12,405
...go into the chamber...

11
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:16,076
...and address the members of the House
and the Senate, Supreme Court...

12
00:01:16,244 --> 00:01:18,161
...the diplomatic corps of Washington...

13
00:01:18,329 --> 00:01:21,122
...all of whom are inside waiting for him
in the chamber.

14
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:27,420
Mr. Speaker,
the president of the United States.

15
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,589
[APPLAUDING AND CHEERING]

16
00:01:34,095 --> 00:01:36,888
ANNOUNCER: And the president,
accompanied by the Escort Committee...

17
00:01:37,056 --> 00:01:41,184
...comes down the central aisle,
approaching the podium.

18
00:01:42,103 --> 00:01:43,770
He greets members of his cabinet...

19
00:01:43,938 --> 00:01:46,648
...and those who are waiting
to be confirmed as members...

20
00:01:46,816 --> 00:01:49,276
...as he reaches the rostrum.

21
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:55,282
Shakes hands with the Speaker,
Carl Albert.

22
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:57,617
A happy president, smiling.

23
00:01:58,869 --> 00:02:01,913
Ladies and gentlemen,
President Nixon will, in a moment...

24
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:06,543
...address the Congress
and the people of the United States.

25
00:02:08,337 --> 00:02:09,921
Thank you.

26
00:02:19,348 --> 00:02:21,349
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

27
00:04:05,621 --> 00:04:07,914
DISPATCHER [OVER RADIO]:
Car 727, Car 727.

28
00:04:08,082 --> 00:04:12,877
Open door at the Watergate office building.
Possible burglary. See the security guard.

29
00:04:13,045 --> 00:04:17,173
Are you sure you want us?
517 is closer, and they're in uniform.

30
00:04:17,341 --> 00:04:19,759
They're getting gas. You take it.

31
00:04:41,949 --> 00:04:44,284
Unit 1 to Unit 2.

32
00:04:45,828 --> 00:04:47,829
Unit 1 to Unit 2.

33
00:04:47,997 --> 00:04:50,957
HUNT [OVER RADIO]: What?
- We're home.

34
00:05:07,892 --> 00:05:10,101
Base 1 to Unit 1.

35
00:05:10,853 --> 00:05:12,896
Base 1 to Unit 1.

36
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:15,523
BALDWIN [OVER RADIO]:
We have some activity here.

37
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:17,192
Silence is advised.

38
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:19,360
[STATIC CRACKLING]

39
00:05:20,738 --> 00:05:22,280
[WHISPERS]
Shut it off.

40
00:05:31,332 --> 00:05:33,541
BALDWIN:
Base 1 to Unit 1.

41
00:05:33,876 --> 00:05:36,085
Lights on the eighth floor.

42
00:05:36,712 --> 00:05:39,088
Base 1 to Unit 1.

43
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:42,091
Is there anybody there?

44
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:51,100
There's people, people on the balcony.
Armed people.

45
00:05:53,354 --> 00:05:55,605
Base 1 to Unit 1.

46
00:05:57,608 --> 00:06:01,236
Base 1 to Unit 1.
We may have some problems.

47
00:06:06,784 --> 00:06:08,701
STURGIS [WHISPERS]:
Someone's here.

48
00:06:34,562 --> 00:06:35,728
OFFICER:
Hold it, you...

49
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:37,313
Police.

50
00:06:37,982 --> 00:06:39,774
Put your hands up.

51
00:06:50,327 --> 00:06:52,287
Drop that jacket.

52
00:06:54,164 --> 00:06:58,710
HARRY:
Walkie-talkie, two 35-mm cameras.

53
00:06:58,877 --> 00:07:03,047
Got it. That's good. All right, stay there.

54
00:07:03,507 --> 00:07:05,550
I got something for you. Did you see this?

55
00:07:05,718 --> 00:07:09,220
Couple sleeping in bed, car hits the house,
goes through their bedroom.

56
00:07:09,388 --> 00:07:12,932
Good morning. Crash.
Louis is over at Democratic headquarters.

57
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:19,564
One of the burglars had $814,
one $230, one $215, and one $234.

58
00:07:19,732 --> 00:07:24,110
Most of it was in $100 bills,
and in sequence.

59
00:07:24,278 --> 00:07:25,486
- Woodward?
BOB: Yup.

60
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:28,406
Break-in at Democratic headquarters.
There's been an arrest.

61
00:07:28,574 --> 00:07:30,908
- Local Democratic headquarters.
- Bugging the place.

62
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:33,369
Check the time of arraignment
and get over there.

63
00:07:33,537 --> 00:07:36,414
And, Woodward,
it was National Democratic Headquarters.

64
00:07:36,582 --> 00:07:37,999
Right.

65
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:41,377
- Anything else?
- Anything else?

66
00:07:41,545 --> 00:07:44,172
Break-in, car crash.
That's not bad for a Saturday.

67
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:45,590
HOWARD:
Let me know what happens.

68
00:07:45,758 --> 00:07:46,799
- Hello, Carl.
CARL: Hi.

69
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:48,009
HOWARD:
Got anything on that couple?

70
00:07:48,177 --> 00:07:50,386
I know somebody on the staff at Watergate.
Want me...?

71
00:07:50,554 --> 00:07:53,514
Why don't you finish one story
before trying to get on another?

72
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:55,308
I finished it.

73
00:07:55,476 --> 00:07:57,685
- The Virginia Legislature story?
- I finished it.

74
00:07:57,853 --> 00:07:59,520
All right, give it to me.

75
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:01,272
I'm just polishing it.

76
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:05,234
- I'll work the phones.
- Polishing it. Yeah, you work the phones.

77
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,988
MAN 1: Who cares?
MAN 2: What about property damage?

78
00:08:09,156 --> 00:08:11,157
BOB: Sorry, who are the lawy...?
Excuse me, sorry.

79
00:08:11,325 --> 00:08:14,202
Who are the lawyers
for the five men arrested at Watergate?

80
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:16,788
- Do you know?
MAN 3: Well, these two were assigned to it.

81
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:17,997
BOB:
Sorry?

82
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:20,208
MAN 3:
These two were appointed to the case.

83
00:08:20,376 --> 00:08:23,378
Only now it turns out
the burglars have their own counsel.

84
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:25,588
- The burglars have their own counsel?
MAN 3: Right.

85
00:08:25,756 --> 00:08:29,592
- That's kind of unusual, wouldn't you say?
MAN 3: For burglars it's unusual.

86
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,386
Do you know the name of the counsel?

87
00:08:31,553 --> 00:08:33,554
MAN 3:
I don't know. Some country-club type.

88
00:08:33,722 --> 00:08:36,265
JUDGE: You are charged
with soliciting prostitution...

89
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:39,143
...at 14th and U Streets Northwest.

90
00:08:39,311 --> 00:08:41,312
[JUDGE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

91
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:45,983
Your Honor,
Mr. Socket has in the past been reliable...

92
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:48,611
...for court appearances when ordered.

93
00:08:48,779 --> 00:08:51,489
I think $300
would subsequently be suggested...

94
00:08:51,657 --> 00:08:53,825
Excuse me, what is your name?

95
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:57,954
I'm Bob Woodward
of the Washington Post.

96
00:08:58,872 --> 00:09:00,581
- Markham.
- Markham?

97
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:04,419
Mr. Markham, are you here in connection
with the Watergate burglary?

98
00:09:05,337 --> 00:09:07,213
I'm not here.

99
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,509
Okay.

100
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:15,888
Well, clearly, I am here...

101
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:19,308
...but only as an individual,
not as the attorney of record.

102
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:21,269
Who is?

103
00:09:21,437 --> 00:09:23,521
Mr. Starkey.

104
00:09:24,148 --> 00:09:26,399
- Do you have any kind of...?
- Whatever you want...

105
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:28,276
...you'll have to get from him.

106
00:09:28,444 --> 00:09:30,570
I have nothing more to say.

107
00:09:39,955 --> 00:09:41,664
Uh, Starkey. S-T...

108
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:47,837
Mr. Starkey was very helpful.

109
00:09:48,005 --> 00:09:52,133
Four Cuban-Americans and another man,
James W. McCord.

110
00:09:52,301 --> 00:09:55,303
Look, I told you inside,
I have nothing more to say.

111
00:09:55,471 --> 00:09:57,388
I understand that.

112
00:09:57,848 --> 00:10:01,142
What I don't understand
is how you got here.

113
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:04,687
I assure you
there's nothing very mysterious involved.

114
00:10:04,855 --> 00:10:07,148
Well, I was talking
to a couple of the lawyers...

115
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:09,400
...assigned to represent the burglars.

116
00:10:09,568 --> 00:10:10,610
So?

117
00:10:10,778 --> 00:10:13,196
They never would've been assigned
to the burglars...

118
00:10:13,363 --> 00:10:16,491
...had anyone known the burglars
had arranged for their own counsel.

119
00:10:16,658 --> 00:10:18,910
The burglars couldn't have
arranged their counsel.

120
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:21,162
They never even made a phone call.

121
00:10:21,914 --> 00:10:25,124
So if no one asked you to be here,
why are you here?

122
00:10:25,709 --> 00:10:28,085
- Don't take this personally, Mr...
- Woodward.

123
00:10:28,253 --> 00:10:32,048
Woodward.
It would be a mistake to do that.

124
00:10:32,216 --> 00:10:33,674
I just don't have anything to say.

125
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:35,843
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

126
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:40,681
ATTORNEY: Your Honor, Mr. Betts
is a young man with no prior record.

127
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:45,770
The defense has suggested a release
on personal bond.

128
00:10:45,938 --> 00:10:49,398
Did one of the other men
involved in the break-in call you?

129
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:53,986
What reason do you have to assume
there were other people involved?

130
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:56,781
One of your clients was arrested
with a walkie-talkie.

131
00:10:56,949 --> 00:10:59,534
They're not my clients.

132
00:11:00,035 --> 00:11:04,038
- I don't wanna talk about this anymore.
- You're a lawyer and you're here.

133
00:11:04,206 --> 00:11:06,896
Well, uh, one of the
defendants, Mr. Barker,

134
00:11:06,897 --> 00:11:09,585
and I met at a social
occasion once.

135
00:11:09,753 --> 00:11:11,254
Where?

136
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:14,131
- I have nothing else to say.
- A Miami social occasion?

137
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:17,677
Mr. Starkey says the Cubans
were from Miami.

138
00:11:17,845 --> 00:11:21,430
L-62, James McCord.
L-63, Bernard Barker.

139
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:24,267
L-64, Virgilio Gonzalez.

140
00:11:24,434 --> 00:11:26,602
L-65, Eugenio Martinez.

141
00:11:26,770 --> 00:11:29,522
L-66, Frank Sturgis.

142
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:34,485
Please step forward, Attorney Starkey.
All charged with burglary two.

143
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:39,490
- And, Mr. Starkey, you represent all five?
STARKEY: Yes, Your Honor.

144
00:11:39,658 --> 00:11:42,910
And are all five gentlemen charged
with burglary in the second degree?

145
00:11:43,078 --> 00:11:44,120
STARKEY:
Yes, Your Honor.

146
00:11:44,288 --> 00:11:46,706
JUDGE: Your names, please,
and state your professions.

147
00:11:47,082 --> 00:11:50,626
BARKER:
Bernard Barker, anti-Communist.

148
00:11:50,794 --> 00:11:55,756
Anti-Communist?
That, sir, is not your average profession.

149
00:11:57,384 --> 00:12:00,469
McCORD:
James McCord, security consultant.

150
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:01,762
JUDGE:
Where?

151
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:05,057
McCORD:
Government. Uh, recently retired.

152
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,976
JUDGE:
Where in the government?

153
00:12:07,144 --> 00:12:09,312
McCORD:
Central Intelligence Agency.

154
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:10,646
Where?

155
00:12:10,814 --> 00:12:12,356
McCORD:
The CIA.

156
00:12:12,983 --> 00:12:16,444
STURGIS:
Sturgis, Frank A., salvage operator.

157
00:12:16,612 --> 00:12:18,821
Holy shit.

158
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:21,824
BOB: Eugenio Martinez,
known as Gene Valdez.

159
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:24,160
James W. McCord, alias Edward Martin.

160
00:12:24,328 --> 00:12:28,039
Frank Sturgis, alias Frank Fiorini.
All five of the men had at least one alias.

161
00:12:28,206 --> 00:12:30,917
Any proof they were trying
to bug the Democratic chairman?

162
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,627
CARL:
It's obvious they were trying to.

163
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:35,171
They wouldn't go to that trouble
to bug secretaries.

164
00:12:35,339 --> 00:12:37,840
- There's no proof.
- I called a lawyer in Miami I know.

165
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:40,801
He said four of the guys that were arrested
were from Miami.

166
00:12:40,969 --> 00:12:42,595
Gonzalez, Martinez, Sturgis and, uh...

167
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:43,804
- Barker.
- Yeah, Barker.

168
00:12:43,972 --> 00:12:46,641
And all four of them were involved
in CIA activities and...

169
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:48,267
BOB: No, only one.
CARL: Yeah, and they...

170
00:12:48,435 --> 00:12:51,729
No, only one of them was admitted CIA,
and the CIA won't confirm that.

171
00:12:51,897 --> 00:12:53,856
In fact, they deny even knowing McCord.

172
00:12:54,024 --> 00:12:56,692
But it's obvious
that with all that money and equipment...

173
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:59,946
...they weren't out to, you know,
work by themselves.

174
00:13:00,113 --> 00:13:01,155
Somebody hired them.

175
00:13:01,323 --> 00:13:03,699
I'm interested in what you know.

176
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,661
We don't know why they wanted
to bug Democratic headquarters.

177
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:10,331
Whether they were working for themselves,
other individuals, organizations.

178
00:13:10,499 --> 00:13:12,249
Could be a story or just crazy Cubans.

179
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:14,418
Bachinski, when you get there,
take it easy.

180
00:13:14,586 --> 00:13:16,253
The police are nervous.

181
00:13:18,048 --> 00:13:20,049
[PHONE RINGING]

182
00:13:25,222 --> 00:13:27,723
- Yeah? BACHINSKI: Calling
from police headquarters.

183
00:13:27,891 --> 00:13:31,352
A friend just showed me what they found
in the hotel rooms of the burglars.

184
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,521
There's something
you might wanna look into.

185
00:13:33,689 --> 00:13:35,064
Hang on.

186
00:13:35,232 --> 00:13:36,232
Okay, go ahead.

187
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,276
There's a strange entry
in two of the burglars' address books.

188
00:13:39,444 --> 00:13:43,197
- Yeah?
- One says "H.H. at W.H."

189
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:45,992
The other says
"Howard Hunt, W. House."

190
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:51,998
BOB: You can dial the White House direct,
can't you?

191
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:53,833
WOMAN 1: Yeah.
- What's the number?

192
00:13:54,001 --> 00:13:57,920
WOMAN 1:
456-1414.

193
00:14:07,848 --> 00:14:10,766
WOMAN 2: White House.
- Howard Hunt, please.

194
00:14:10,934 --> 00:14:13,019
Mr. Hunt isn't here just now.

195
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:16,772
He might be in Mr. Colson's office.
I'll connect you.

196
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:18,607
Thank you.

197
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:21,569
WOMAN 3: Charles Colson's office.
- Howard Hunt, please.

198
00:14:21,737 --> 00:14:23,612
Mr. Hunt isn't here just now.

199
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:26,907
- Do you know when he'll be back?
- No, I don't.

200
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:28,117
Okay, thank you.

201
00:14:28,285 --> 00:14:30,661
- Have you tried the Mullen firm?
- I beg your pardon?

202
00:14:30,829 --> 00:14:33,831
He also works as a writer
at Mullen and Company Public Relations.

203
00:14:33,999 --> 00:14:37,752
- You have a phone on that or an address?
- No, I don't. I'm sorry.

204
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,295
All right, thank you.

205
00:14:40,088 --> 00:14:42,882
WOMAN 4: Do you know
in a survey taken, 10.9 percent...?

206
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:44,508
Harry.

207
00:14:44,968 --> 00:14:46,427
Who's Charles Colson?

208
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:50,306
Who's Charles Colson?

209
00:14:50,474 --> 00:14:51,974
Sit down.

210
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:54,602
I'm glad you asked me that question.

211
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:57,938
The reason I'm glad is because
if you had asked Simons or Bradlee...

212
00:14:58,106 --> 00:14:59,148
...they would've said:

213
00:14:59,316 --> 00:15:03,319
"You know, we're gonna have to fire this
schmuck at once because he's so dumb."

214
00:15:03,487 --> 00:15:04,862
Who is Charles Colson?

215
00:15:06,073 --> 00:15:09,533
The most powerful man
in the United States is President Nixon.

216
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:11,077
You've heard of him?

217
00:15:12,788 --> 00:15:15,915
Charles Colson is special counsel
to the president.

218
00:15:16,083 --> 00:15:18,125
There's a cartoon on his wall.

219
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:22,088
Caption reads,
"When you've got them by the balls...

220
00:15:22,255 --> 00:15:24,173
...their hearts and minds will follow."

221
00:15:24,341 --> 00:15:26,509
WOMAN 5:
Do you have a list of receipts?

222
00:15:27,385 --> 00:15:30,596
IVY: Hello, Mr. Murray?
This is Ivy Mills of the Washington Post.

223
00:15:30,764 --> 00:15:31,847
I'd like to know if...

224
00:15:32,015 --> 00:15:33,015
WOMAN 6:
Mullen and Company.

225
00:15:33,183 --> 00:15:36,393
- Howard Hunt, please.
- One moment, please.

226
00:15:36,561 --> 00:15:38,354
HUNT:
Howard Hunt here.

227
00:15:39,314 --> 00:15:41,857
Hi, I'm Bob Woodward
of the Washington Post.

228
00:15:42,025 --> 00:15:44,110
Yes. Yes, what is it?

229
00:15:44,277 --> 00:15:46,779
I was just wondering
why your name and phone number...

230
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:50,658
...were in the address books
of two of the men arrested at Watergate.

231
00:15:50,826 --> 00:15:52,118
Good God.

232
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:55,704
- Do you care to comment?
- The matter is under adjudication.

233
00:15:55,872 --> 00:15:57,581
I have no comment.

234
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:01,043
WOMAN 7 [OVER PHONE]: Hello?
BOB: This is Bob Woodward...

235
00:16:01,211 --> 00:16:02,419
...of the Washington Post.

236
00:16:02,587 --> 00:16:05,798
I was told that you had worked
with a Mr. Howard Hunt.

237
00:16:05,966 --> 00:16:07,258
Why would anyone say that?

238
00:16:08,051 --> 00:16:09,718
You do know Mr. Hunt?

239
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:11,053
