594
00:40:30,137 --> 00:40:32,013
Follow the money.

595
00:40:34,224 --> 00:40:35,850
What do you mean?

596
00:40:36,727 --> 00:40:38,853
- Where?
- Oh, I can't tell you that.

597
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:41,314
But you could tell me, then.

598
00:40:42,357 --> 00:40:44,817
No, I have to do this my way.

599
00:40:44,985 --> 00:40:48,487
You tell me what you know,
and I'll confirm.

600
00:40:48,655 --> 00:40:52,950
I'll keep you in the right direction
if I can, but that's all.

601
00:40:55,912 --> 00:40:58,914
Just follow the money.

602
00:41:08,884 --> 00:41:12,178
CARL: Goddamn New York Times.
BOB: What is it?

603
00:41:13,388 --> 00:41:17,642
CARL: Phone calls from the burglars
in Miami to the Committee to Reelect.

604
00:41:20,771 --> 00:41:22,229
BOB:
Fifteen phone calls.

605
00:41:22,397 --> 00:41:25,107
CARL: At least 15 phone calls,
and those phone calls were made...

606
00:41:25,275 --> 00:41:28,069
...as early as March 15th,
three months before the break-in.

607
00:41:28,236 --> 00:41:31,906
BOB: "Eighty-nine thousand dollars issued
in the name of a prominent Mexican lawyer."

608
00:41:32,074 --> 00:41:34,867
Eighty-nine thousand dollars
in Mexican checks?

609
00:41:35,035 --> 00:41:36,994
Why didn't we get this?

610
00:41:37,913 --> 00:41:38,954
Who are their sources?

611
00:41:39,122 --> 00:41:41,999
I even know someone
who works on the phone company.

612
00:41:43,085 --> 00:41:45,419
Carl, if John Mitchell
wanted your phone records...

613
00:41:45,587 --> 00:41:47,546
...you'd be yelling invasion of privacy.

614
00:41:47,714 --> 00:41:49,590
Was the New York Times article accurate?

615
00:41:49,758 --> 00:41:52,259
- Yeah, but I can't get you
a fuller listing. - Why?

616
00:41:52,427 --> 00:41:54,720
They've subpoenaed
all of Barker's phone records.

617
00:41:54,888 --> 00:41:59,433
I think they're trying to find out if the
Watergate burglars broke any Florida law.

618
00:42:00,519 --> 00:42:02,520
- Who subpoenaed them?
- Miami DA.

619
00:42:02,688 --> 00:42:04,689
- What's his name?
- I don't know his name.

620
00:42:04,856 --> 00:42:07,608
But the guy who's heading the investigation
is named Dardis.

621
00:42:07,776 --> 00:42:10,194
Dardis. What's his first name?

622
00:42:10,362 --> 00:42:14,198
I don't know his first name.
I guess you'll have to find that out.

623
00:42:14,366 --> 00:42:16,367
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

624
00:42:21,123 --> 00:42:22,164
CARL: Hi.
MIRIAM: Hello.

625
00:42:22,332 --> 00:42:24,458
I have a 9:15 appointment
with Mr. Dardis.

626
00:42:24,626 --> 00:42:28,337
Mr. Bernstein, I'm afraid that Mr. Dardis
won't be able to see you this morning.

627
00:42:28,505 --> 00:42:31,006
- His calendar is quite full.
- There must be a mistake.

628
00:42:31,174 --> 00:42:33,134
I made the appointment
with him personally.

