00:42:33,301 --> 00:42:35,469
The appointment should've been made
through me.

630
00:42:35,637 --> 00:42:37,680
I'll see if I can squeeze you in later.

631
00:42:37,848 --> 00:42:39,890
Oh, thanks very much.

632
00:42:40,934 --> 00:42:45,104
I guess it's difficult
when he makes his own appointments.

633
00:42:45,272 --> 00:42:48,149
Yes, well, we try to handle it.

634
00:42:55,991 --> 00:42:59,493
GUARD: It's 4:00. We'll be back
in 15 minutes. Do you want anything?

635
00:42:59,661 --> 00:43:02,580
- Coffee, black.
GUARD: Coffee, black.

636
00:43:07,210 --> 00:43:08,836
I'm still here.

637
00:43:09,004 --> 00:43:10,546
Ha, ha. I'm so glad.

638
00:43:10,714 --> 00:43:13,424
If you could get me in for five minutes,
I'd appreciate it.

639
00:43:13,592 --> 00:43:16,469
- Mr. Bernstein.
- I have to get back.

640
00:43:16,636 --> 00:43:18,721
We're going to try.

641
00:43:21,183 --> 00:43:23,684
Oh, hi. He's expecting you.

642
00:43:28,857 --> 00:43:30,357
I do have a couple things to do.

643
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:33,110
I'll be at the Sheraton
if you wanna reach me.

644
00:43:33,278 --> 00:43:36,363
If he has space tomorrow,
I'd appreciate it. Number's on the back.

645
00:43:36,531 --> 00:43:38,365
- Fine.
- I thank you for your patience.

646
00:43:38,533 --> 00:43:42,578
Mm-hm. Thank you, Mr. Bernstein.
Tomorrow it should be better.

647
00:43:42,746 --> 00:43:44,747
I guess so.

648
00:43:48,710 --> 00:43:49,752
WOMAN:
Mr. Dardis' office.

649
00:43:49,920 --> 00:43:53,506
Hi. Please tell Mr. Dardis
