650
00:43:53,673 --> 00:43:55,841
He'll be available all day tomorrow.

651
00:43:56,009 --> 00:43:58,803
I think we can probably squeeze him in
around 4:30.

652
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:00,012
WOMAN: Yes.
- Mm-hm.

653
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:03,974
And please tell Mr. Dardis he doesn't want
to be late for his 6:30 appointment.

654
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:06,644
- Yes, I will.
- Mm-hm. Thank you.

655
00:44:09,397 --> 00:44:12,191
[PHONE RINGS]

656
00:44:14,152 --> 00:44:16,862
- Mr. Dardis' office.
CARL: Mr. Martinson at the county clerk's.

657
00:44:17,030 --> 00:44:19,365
- Beg your pardon?
- Martinson at the county clerk's.

658
00:44:19,533 --> 00:44:23,410
There's some records that Dardis wanted.
Could you come get them? We're closing.

659
00:44:23,578 --> 00:44:26,080
Uh, well, yes, I'll be right over.

660
00:44:31,628 --> 00:44:33,254
Excuse me.

661
00:44:50,981 --> 00:44:52,606
DARDIS:
Would be easier too, wouldn't it?

662
00:44:52,774 --> 00:44:55,734
All right. Hold it. What?

663
00:44:55,902 --> 00:44:57,736
CARL: Excuse me.
